## ⚡ MANDATORY: Quality Pipeline

### After Every Code Change

#### 1. Pre-Change (DB Changes Only)
```bash
read_file src/integrations/supabase/types.ts  # Check schema/relationships
```

#### 2. Code Quality
```bash
npm run lint    # Check for NEW errors only
npm run build   # MUST pass
```

#### 3. Browser Testing
```bash
pkill -f "vite"                              # Kill existing servers
# USER starts: npm run dev (in their terminal)
sleep 3 && curl localhost:8080              # Verify startup
mcp_playwright_browser_navigate http://localhost:8080
mcp_playwright_browser_console_messages     # Check for errors
mcp_playwright_browser_snapshot             # Visual verification
```

#### 4. Flow Testing
- ✅ Login/navigation works
- ✅ Forms validate correctly  
- ✅ Loading states display
- ✅ Error handling works
- ✅ Mobile responsive
- ✅ Touch targets ≥44px
- ✅ Console has no errors

#### 5. Documentation
```bash
edit_file development-log.md  # Log changes
```

### Quality Gates (All Must Pass)
- [ ] `npm run build` succeeds
- [ ] Browser console clean
- [ ] Complete user flow tested
- [ ] Design principles applied
- [ ] Multi-tenant security verified

